# Project Rules

`AGENTS.md`/`CLAUDE.md`, `.agents/rules/`/`.claude/rules/`/`.cursor/rules/`, and `SECURITY.md` are the source of truth for project-specific (non-behavioral) rules.

## Before you edit

1. `AGENTS.md`/`CLAUDE.md` — behavioral guidelines (mirrored above), plus an index into the per-topic rule files below for architecture, feature layout, auth/API conventions, verification, and documenting work
2. `SECURITY.md` — security policy and guidelines; full risk register in `docs/security/*.md`
3. `README.md` — install, usage, CLI commands, runtime config, API expectations, or operational workflow changes

For auth work, also read `docs/plans/auth-implementation.md` and `docs/plans/auth-security.md`. Docs layout: `docs/README.md`.

